{
  "stem": "2067.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Then, when you have your-- your-- your high school degree, you-- you can try again to be admitted to school here.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But, my dear boy, you will have to start from scratch.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Since my father, as I mentioned before, did not speak French, and neither one of us spoke Spanish, there was only one possibility to earn a living.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that was that I took over and advised my father, and not only advise him, but I was the one who started to build up a new business once we had decided not to go back.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "By the summer of that same year, 1933, my brother, my mother, and both married sisters with their families came to Spain, because the-- the anti-Semitic decrees started making life already difficult for Jews in Germany, in-- as far as earning a living was concerned.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So at least we-- our family was together in Barcelona.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] It took me approximately six month to learn Spanish.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I learned it rather fluently, very much helped by my knowledge of Latin.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] So did my brother, he learned the-- the language very quickly.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we both became the-- the earners of a living, since my father was only able to advise us, and-- because of his experience.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] In the summer of 1936, the-- the Spanish Civil War broke out.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "From that time on, import of eggs was no longer possible.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And that forced us to start butter business.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "The republic of Spain had no foreign currency, so imports were only allowed if, in turn, you could export Spanish products, and then use that foreign currency, that money, to import essential and necessary products from those countries.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And that's exactly what we did.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
